*[[Erena Ono]] as Eimi Mitsushima
*[[Mitsuki Tanimura]] as Minori Maetani (Miki's friend from university)
*[[Shihori Kanjiya]] as Yuko Tanimura (Miki's childhood friend)
*[[Shunsuke Daito]] as Shingo Eto (Miki's ex-middle school friend)
*[[Misako Renbutsu]] as Risako Kano 
*[[Shōta Sometani]] as Hasegawa
*[[Dankan]] as Kozaburo Shirono (Miki's father)
*[[Yoko Akino]] as atsuki Shirono (Miki's mother)
*[[Mao Miyaji]] as Mayama

==Music==
*"All Alone in the World" performed by [[Serizawa Brothers]] (Tsukemen)

==Reception==
The film earned {{JPY|1 billion}} (US$8,646,060) in Japan.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.eiren.org/toukei/img/eiren_kosyu/data_2014.pdf|title= ２０１４年 （平成２６年） 全国映画概況|accessdate= October 31, 2015|work= eiren.org|publisher= Motion Picture Producers Association of Japan, Inc.|language= Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://boxofficemojo.com/intl/japan/?yr=2014&wk=17&p=.htm|title= Japan Box Office April 26–27, 2014|accessdate= 30 April 2014|work= [[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref>

Patryk Czekaj, in a review on [[Twitch Film]], called the film "one of the most compelling crime thrillers to come out of Japan in the last few years".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://twitchfilm.com/2014/05/udine-2014-review-the-snow-white-murder-case-gives-a-stunning-new-angle-to-familiar-thriller-formula.html|title=  Udine 2014 Review: THE SNOW WHITE MURDER CASE Gives A Stunning New Angle To Familiar Thriller Formula|author= Patryk Czekaj|date= May 2014|accessdate= 5 May 2014|work= [[Twitch Film]]}}</ref>

